</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="95" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Gecarcinidae" genus="Gecarcinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gecarcinus" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gecarcinus</taxonomicName>
Leach, 1814: 430.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="95" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cancer ruricola" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruricola">Cancer ruricola</taxonomicName>
Linnaeus, 1758 (original combination).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Exopod not projecting beyond third maxilliped ischium-merus articulation, without flagellum; palp concealed by third maxilliped merus margin. Mesial segment of first male gonopod distally reduced and terminal segment basally exposed, terminal segment projecting beyond apical setae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="95" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
Because further evidence challenging 
<bibRefCitation author="Tuerkay, M" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Museum D'Histoire Naturelle, Paris" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" pagination="969 - 980" title="Bemerkungen zu einigen Landkrabben." volume="142" year="1973">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Türkay’s">Tuerkay's</normalizedToken>
(1973)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymization of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Gecarcinidae" genus="Gecarcinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gecarcinus quadratus" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratus">Gecarcinus quadratus</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Gecarcinidae" genus="Gecarcinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gecarcinus lateralis" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">Gecarcinus lateralis</taxonomicName>
has not been presented to date, we follow his taxonomy and treat 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Gecarcinidae" genus="Gecarcinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gecarcinus quadratus" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratus">Gecarcinus quadratus</taxonomicName>
, described from the Pacific mainland, as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Gecarcinidae" genus="Gecarcinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gecarcinus lateralis" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">Gecarcinus lateralis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
